Stay at home
Only go outside for food, health reasons or work (but only if you cannot work from home)
If you go out, stay 2 metres (6ft) away from other people at all times
Wash your hands as soon as you get home
Do not meet others, even friends or family.
You can spread the virus even if you donâ€™t have symptoms.

There are currently no commercial options available to return to the UK from Guinea Bissau. All borders and commercial air links are closed.
What to do
If you cannot leave Guinea Bissau at this time, you should:
Follow the advice of the local authorities, including local measures to help minimise your risk of exposure to coronavirus;
Find accommodation suitable for your needs;
Keep in regular contact with family and friends at home, so they know you are safe and well.
Future travel options
It may be possible to leave on a European repatriation flight. If you are a UK visitor who is normally resident in the UK and you want to leave Guinea Bissau, please contact the British Embassy Dakar, which covers Guinea Bissau, on Facebook or Twitter (@UKinSenegal). This travel advice will be updated when departure options become available.
Sign up for travel advice email alerts and follow the British Embassy Dakar on Facebook or Twitter (@UKinSenegal).
Help and support
If you need urgent consular assistance, you can contact the British Embassy Dakar on Facebook or Twitter (@UKinSenegal).
The Embassy cannot provide further information or advice about departure options over the phone. This page will be updated when departure options become available. To get the latest information, sign up for travel advice email alerts.
See additional advice on making travel plans to return to the UK, or what to do if you cannot depart immediately.
